latestPosts.caption:
🧋comment “link” for my beauty drink & PCOS elixir recipes 🧋

Don’t be fooled by everything you see on the internet including this reel. This is my ideal morning routine, which helped heal my chronic stress, but there are some days where I can’t wake up on time or I don’t have enough time to do everything. I don’t beat myself up over anymore, I simply accept things the way they are, and try to do my best. 

The root cause of PCOS  is stress, & striving for perfection in your routines will further stress you out. Pick three things at a time & romanticise each of them while doing it. 

The art of de-stressing is to slow down, and savour each moment, and each aspect of your routine. 

A few other things I enjoy is spending  time each morning making my beauty drinks to begin my day positively. These include my beauty matcha, protein shakes, my PCOS elixirs (comment “tea” and I’ll send you the recipe) and making a list for the days work. This was I don’t get overwhelmed and stressed. 

Let me know if you’d like to see a PM routine dedicated to reversing & healing my PCOS & related hair fall, stress and acne 🩷🫶🏼

#pcosrecipes #pcosweightloss #healthyhairtips #pcosawareness #explore #slowliving #wellnessgirlie #wellnessliving #skincareisselfcare #slowingdown

Another day, another episode of”Not sponsored, I’m just a fan”🙆🏻‍♀️

Period pain has plagued me to the point of asking 3 different gynaecologists for a hysterectomy. Anyone with endometriosis or adenomyosis knows the debilitating pain, the body acne, the fatigue, the migraines and general reduction in quality of life is truly indescribable. 

I’ve spent the last few months trying to naturally reduce pain and find ways to improve my menstrual flow, and while it’s never 100%, the cramping and pain have reduced significantly, to the point that I feel comfortable sharing my opinions here. 

I’ve also visited many holistic and Chinese medicine doctors and under their guidance made of lifestyle changes that have helped with period pain and overall hormonal issues, let me know if you would a video on that🫶🏼

latestPosts.caption:
🧔🏽‍♀️🧔🏻‍♀️ if that looks like you, it’s time to start incorporating stinging nettle & spearmint tea into your wellness routine. 

Comment “tea” for the link to shop my favourites from @teatrunk which I’ve been drinking for close to a year now 🌷

Spearmint’s anti-androgen properties help with high testosterone in women (aka the cause of facial hair/ hirsutism) and other PCOS symptoms like oily skin. It naturally lowers DHT, aka the hormone causing hair loss and it reduces oil production on the scalp and face. 
Spearmint tea could be the the secret to lesser breakouts, better hair, a cleaner scalp and oil free skin. 

Nettle tea reduces inflammation in the body and the skin, so when you have an itchy scalp, active cystic acne or even severe joint pain, incorporating nettle tea could help in your daily wellness rituals. 

Enjoy a cup or two a few times a week and don’t forget to stay consistent for results 🌸🌼

Leave a comment below for links and let me me know if you want my acne prone skin night routine 😇

All products are bought and tested by me for weeks before recommending🥰

🩷 Step 1 @gunambeauty toner is a gentle exfoliant with natural fruit extracts, calming aloe Vera and chamomile, brightening and plumping niacinamide and hyaluronic acid so this one is literally an all round legend of a product.

🩷 Step 2 @laneige_in cream skin toner gives me actual glass skin. If you don’t feel like wearing make-up this is the toner that plumps and brightens skin.  Not recommended for people with cystic acne. Personally, this is the OG glass skin toner! Available on @tira

🩷 @froika_gr Anti pigment multiply serum with vitamin C for skin brightening. Recommended by my dermatologist in Dubai , this is what helps with acne marks and dark spots as well as hyper pigmentation which many of us with brown skin experience. Unfortunately it’s not available in India, so you can contact @athenaderma to purchase the product or talk to your dermatologist to find something similar. 

@skin1004official @skin1004_india tea tree sunscreen🤌🏼🤌🏼Ever since I started using this I’ve noticed less active acne popping up and an even skin tone. The entire skin 1004 tea tree line and tone brightening line is incredible! 

My morning routine goal is to reduce hyperpigmentation, prevent sun damage, and also have plum hydrated skin. My evening skincare routine focuses on reducing active acne, fine lines and anti-aging. 

Let me know if you want to see that routine too 🩵

Benefits of matcha for strong hair and glowing skin

💚Apparently no kids aka less stress🤷🏻‍♀️
🤍High in antioxidants therefore bright, glowing skin
💚L-theanine in matcha strengthens hair follicles
🤍 DHT blocker in green teas prevent hair fall 
💚protects against sun damage 
🤍boosts collagen production so expect plumper skin 

My fav matcha at the moment is @yuzen.matcha and @glow_glossary
